review_comments.body:
I know this behavior predated you, @keithduncan, but I'd still like to discuss it: should keys in the document win over keys in the params? I think params should be the winner and this merge should be reversed.

Elasticsearch normally ignores special keys in documents. Elastomer allows users to cheat a bit, but the cheating shouldn't override the official behavior. The params hash should be authoritative if it exists and there is a conflict. I think this is what elastomer users are likely to expect: that the params hash is more of an override than the document hash. This mirrors the behavior of search requests, where the params hash overrides the request body.

@TwP what are your thoughts?

