review_comments.body:
This might create a race condition between the `create` call above and then the `udpate_mapping` call here. Another approach would be to create a `mappings` hash and then add the percolator section when testing under ES 5.X.

```ruby
mappings = {
   # doc1 and doc2 go here
}

if es_version_5_x?
  mappings[:percolator] = { ... }
end

@index.create \
  :settings => { ... },
  :mappings => mappings
```

Or something like that.

